narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A small class, that's really as valuable as you make it. Adel's critical perspective can make you a lot less assuming and a lot smarter as well. Seminar-like, the class allows you to improve you understanding of issues in the Middle East from their basis in the earlier centuries of Islam. Give it a shop, it's a good class.
Take the course if you'd like to get a more in-depth view of the beginning of Islamic history.
